    {
      "slug": "youtube-filter-pro",
      "chromeExtensionId": "dbkkcbfafkckhmefkpgnelikibobcabb",
      "name": "Youtube Filter Pro: filter by views, duration, date, and more",
      "icon": "⚡",
      "chromeExtensionIcon": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/cT5IsRijPKr64wr862UQQHyrC1A2YsAaG4JM9fTE4OAiwLxxMfTmEqUG0HsFW9TdB2CQtotPwmSdFldxRvpG3pyOTg",
      "tagline": "Filter YouTube search results in real time by duration, views, publish date, channel, and more.",
      "status": "live",
      "price": "Free",
      "revenue": "$0",
      "chromeStoreUrl": "https://chromewebstore.google.com/detail/dbkkcbfafkckhmefkpgnelikibobcabb",
      "version": "1.0.03",
      "lastUpdated": "2026-06-06",
      "category": "Productivity",
      "platform": "Google Chrome",
      "description": {
        "short": "Have you ever wanted to filter youtube videos by length of time? Maybe show videos only between 2 minutes and 3 minutes? Perhaps by views? Only videos between 10k-20k views? Or include exclusively videos that has a certain keyword in the title?",
        "full": "Have you ever wanted to filter youtube videos by length of time? Maybe show videos only between 2 minutes and 3 minutes? Perhaps by views? Only videos between 10k-20k views? Or include exclusively videos that has a certain keyword in the title?\n\nNow you can!\n\nYoutube Filter Pro adds powerful, client-side filters to YouTube search, so you can narrow results without running a new search or clicking through YouTube’s limited built-in filters.\n\nHOW IT WORKS\n\n• On any YouTube page, click the Filters button in the top bar (next to the search controls).\n• Run a search as usual — filtering applies on the search results page.\n• Videos that don’t match your criteria are hidden or faded in place, in real time, as results load and as you scroll.\n• Your filter settings are saved and restored automatically across sessions (synced via Chrome).\n\nFILTER BY\n\n📅 Publish date — Quick presets from “last hour” up to “last 10 years,” or pick a custom date range.\n\n⏱ Duration — Set minimum and maximum length (hours, minutes, seconds). Great for finding tutorials, podcasts, or short clips.\n\n👁 View count — Show only videos within a view range (e.g. smaller channels or already-popular uploads).\n\n📺 Channel — Include channels whose names contain certain keywords, or block specific channels with exclude tags.\n\n📝 Title — Require keywords in the title, or exclude unwanted terms (e.g. “reaction,” “short,” “live”).\n\n✓ Verified — Show only verified channels, hide verified channels, or leave unchanged.\n\nFEATURES\n\n• Real-time filtering as search results appear — including infinite scroll\n• Clean filter panel that doesn’t clash with YouTube’s layout\n• One-click enable/disable filtering without losing your settings\n• Optional active-filter summary in the panel\n• Lightweight: only needs storage permission; no account required\n\nWHO IT’S FOR\n\n• Researchers and learners who need recent or in-depth videos\n• Creators scouting topics by duration or popularity\n• Anyone tired of scrolling past irrelevant channels, reuploads, or off-topic titles\n\nPRIVACY\n\nYoutube Filter Pro runs only on youtube.com. It uses Chrome storage to remember your filter preferences. It does not collect personal data or send your searches to external servers.\n\nQuestions or feedback? Use the support link on this listing."
      },
