      "description": {
        "short": "Right-click file links and images on any page to upload them straight to a folder in your Google Drive. Files are not downloaded locally.",
        "full": "Right-click file links and images on any page to upload them straight to a folder in your Google Drive. Files are not downloaded locally.\n\nHow it works\n\n- Install the extension and click Connect Google Drive in the popup.\n- Right-click a file link or image on almost any website.\n- Choose \"Save to Google Drive\"\n- A small on-page message confirms progress; when it’s done, open the file in Drive with one click.\n\nFeatures\n\n- Right-click to save: works on file links and images across the web\n- Your folder: choose where files go in Drive (default: “Downloads”)\n- Rename before save: optional dialog to edit the filename before upload\n- Recent saves: quickly reopen your last uploads from the extension popup\n- Open Google Drive: one click from the popup to your Drive\n- Supports all major image formats\n\nFeatures coming soon (not coded yet)\n- Website to PDF and JPG => Google Drive - coming soon!\n- Gmail to PDF => Google Drive - coming soon!\n\nPrivacy & permissions\n\n- Files go only to your Google account. nothing is stored on third-party servers.\n- Saves happen only when you ask, nothing uploads in the background.\n- The extension uses Google’s drive.file scope: it can upload files you choose, but cannot browse, edit, or delete your existing Drive files.\n- Log out anytime from the extension menu.\n\nRequirements\nA Google account with Google Drive."
      },
